## 8. Database Model (Optional - for metadata)

### Table: `product_embeddings`

**Migration**: `/src/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_create_product_embeddings_table.ts`

```typescript
export async function up(knex: Knex): Promise<void> {
  await knex.schema.createTable('product_embeddings', (table) => {
    table.uuid('_id').primary();
    table.integer('style_id').unsigned().notNullable().unique();
    table.text('description').notNullable(); // Product description used
    table.string('model', 100).notNullable().defaultTo('text-embedding-3-small');
    table.integer('dimensions').unsigned().notNullable().defaultTo(1536);
    table.timestamp('created_at').notNullable().defaultTo(knex.fn.now());
    table.timestamp('updated_at').notNullable().defaultTo(knex.fn.now());
    table.timestamp('deleted_at').nullable();

    // Indexes
    table.index('style_id', 'idx_product_embeddings_style_id');
    table.index('updated_at', 'idx_product_embeddings_updated_at');

    // Foreign key
    table.foreign('style_id').references('style_id').inTable('styles');
  });
}
```

**Why NOT store embeddings in DB**:
- Embedding vectors (1536 floats × 4 bytes = 6KB per row) would bloat database
- Not optimized for vector similarity queries
- Binary file in memory is faster
- Database stores metadata only (tracking, versioning)

**Model Interface**: `/src/modules/db/product-embeddings/types/product-embedding.base.interface.ts`

```typescript
